==English==

===Idiom===
'''[[have]] [[a]] [[chip]] [[on]] [[one's]] [[shoulder]]'''

# {{idiom}} {{pos_vi}} To have a habitually combative attitude, usually because of a perception of having something to prove.
#:''He really '''has a chip on his shoulder''' about being passed over for that promotion.''

Also, to insert a tube into the anus so that a gerbil or other small rodent can crawl inside.  This is used for anal sexual pleasure. (also known as gerbiling, or gerbil stuffing)